HEADWORD: Photo-epinasty
<hw>Pho`to-ep"i*nas`ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Photo-</er>, and <er>Epinastic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
disproportionately rapid growth of the upper surface of dorsiventral
organs, such as leaves, through the stimulus of exposure to light.</def>
<rj><au>Encyc. Brit.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
